race.comment: HARLEQUIN PRANCER (3) is racing well this time in work, though she was just too far back to threaten over 1300m last time out. Out to 1400m now should suit her better now and she's better than what she showed last start. Can get back to her best and return to winning ways. GOLDEN OPERA (8) broke her maiden here last start in good order and looks better suited again getting out to the 1400m journey. She closed off strongly from midfield to win as the favourite, though she has drawn wider this time around. Still has plenty of upside however and can repeat the dose. SAFE RAPPA (11) is better than he showed last start when 80-1 at Mt Barker last time out. This looks to suit him a little better back to this level and he'll carry no weight after the claim. Can bounce back. METALIC MARLIN (5) has claims coming back in trip. PRAY FOR LUCY (12) finds a suitable race on resumption and can feature.
